It's all in the cloud, so it doesn't matter because in the Zero Trust architecture, we don't put users on the network. We connect them like a switchboard,\" says Chaudhry. As part of\u00a0part of\u00a0Yahoo Finance's exclusive coverage\u00a0from the World Economic Forum in Davos, Switzerland,\u00a0Yahoo Finance's\u00a0Julie Hyman\u00a0and\u00a0Brian Sozzi spoke to preeminent leaders and top executives across the industry about advancements in AI and expectations for the coming year. The advancements in artificial intelligence, generative AI in particular, have had a\u00a0major impact on the work of the Bill and Melinda Gates Foundation.\u00a0\"I found it's a real productivity increase,\"\u00a0former Microsoft (MSFT) President and CEO Bill Gates\u00a0explained. \"Likewise, for coders, you're seeing 40, 50% productivity improvement, which means you can get programs sooner. You can make them higher quality, make them better.\" Nasdaq (NDAQ)\u00a0CEO and President Adena Friedman\u00a0broke down the impact of AI on new companies entering the market.\u00a0Friedman said, \"Very exciting time, I have to say, because every company can benefit from this next generation of technology. I think you can look at every industry and gen AI has applicability. So companies that help unlock that potential are going to be, I think, companies that a lot of investors are looking at.\" Bank of America\u00a0(BAC)\u00a0CEO Brian Moynihan provided his thoughts on AI applications.\u00a0Moynihan said, \"We completely believe that this will have a big impact ... you have to have the ability to convert processes to technique through language models and learning models. The trick in that is that we have to have accountability.\" The popularity of generative AI will impact companies like Verizon Communications (VZ), which controls the wireless networks which will transmit so much of this data.\u00a0Verizon Chairman and CEO Hans Vestberg said, \"I think at the edge of the network it's going to be very important to have AI to take quick decisions very close to the end views of the customer or the enterprise. And of course that's how we build our network.\" Novartis (NVS) recently announced a partnership with Alphabet (GOOG, GOOGL) and also has an existing partnership with Microsoft, which\u00a0leverages its AI platform.\u00a0Novartis CEO Vasant Narasimhan explained, \"We developed an approach called generative chemistry to try to speed up how fast we can bring new medicines into the clinic ... it's really opening up new horizons.\" Cisco (CSCO) CEO Chuck Robbins discussed the trajectory of AI and the impact it will have across the industry.\u00a0Robbins said, \"I think the ones that are going to win are the ones that figure out how do I create value based capabilities that help end users take advantage of the data they have.\" Salesforce (CRM) CEO Marc Benioff believes that we will one day have AI employees, but we are not there yet.\u00a0Benioff said, \"There's no question that where AI is going is digital employees ... in today's world that's not where AI is. We know that AI has got a lot of problems still.\" Qualcomm (QCOM) CEO Cristiano Amon broke down\u00a0the state of the semiconductor sector given the surge in AI demand.\u00a0Amon explained, \"It's so exciting we did something that is very unique. We can run those large language models on your phone, and you can do them very fast.\" Microsoft has plans\u00a0to expand its AI capabilities.\u00a0Microsoft Vice Chair and President Brad Smith said, \"I think this is one technology that will live up to the impact that people expect ... it is quite possibly the defining technology of our lifetime, certainly this decade I think without question.\" C3.ai (AI) Founder, Chairman, and CEO Tom Siebel discussed his\u00a0expectations for AI products as more companies pivot into the space.\u00a0Siebel said, \"Generative AI changes everything. It fundamentally changes the nature of the human-computer interface as it relates to enterprise application software, and this is big.\" Williams-Sonoma\u00a0(WSM) is utilizing\u00a0AI in its\u00a0email marketing\u00a0as well as its supply chain optimization.\u00a0Williams-Sonoma CEO Laura Alber explained, \"We're seeing great benefit on the supply chain side being optimized. And we can optimize it for time, or we can optimize it for cost.\" Grammy Award-winning musician and entrepreneur will.i.am announced a new radio show he will be co-hosting with an AI co-host.
